    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1934-02-09T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1934-02-09T00:00:00-05:00" n="640"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d640">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">576.G1/1</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Secretary General of the League of Nations</hi> (<persName
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Avenol</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                    <note n="1" xml:id="d640fn1">This circular letter was transmitted to the
                        Department by the Minister in Switzerland in his despatch No. 3242 (L. N.
                        No. 2608), February 10; received March 1.</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. C. L. 17.1934.XII</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>The Secretary-General of the League of Nations, in pursuance of a resolution
                    adopted by the Council of the League of Nations on January 15th, 1934,<note
                        n="2" xml:id="d640fn2">See League of Nations, <hi rend="italic">Official
                            Journal</hi>, February 1934, pp. 109–110.</note> has the honour to
                    transmit to the Government of United States of America, for its observations, a
                    preliminary draft International Agreement for the Use of Broadcasting in the
                    Cause of Peace.<note n="3" xml:id="d640fn3">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 170.</note>
                </p>
                <p>This preliminary draft, accompanied by an explanatory note,<note n="4"
                        xml:id="d640fn4">
                        <hi rend="italic">Ibid.</hi>, p. 168.</note> has been drawn up by the
                    Intellectual Co-operation Organisation in accordance with the directions given
                    to it by the Assembly of the League of Nations.</p>
                <p>In instructing the Secretary-General to communicate this draft agreement to the
                    Governments Members and non-members of the League of Nations, the Council asked
                    him to request those Governments to send in any observations they might wish to
                    make by August 1st, 1934.</p>
                <closer>
                    <dateline rendition="#left">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1934-02-09">February 9,
                            1934</date>.</dateline>
                </closer>
            </div>
